ty%20of%20the%0A%20%20pink%20noise%20family%20of%20waveforms.%20The%20top%20box%20is%20an%20oscilloscope%20view%0A%20%20which%20visualizes%20the%20waveform%2C%20and%20the%20bottom%20box%20is%20a%20harmonic%0A%20%20spectrum%20view.%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%0A%3Cp%3E%0A%20%20Pink%20noise%20is%20characterized%20as%20having%20a%20harmonic%20curve%20where%20amplitude%0A%20%20slopes%20down%20from%20low%20to%20high%20frequencies.%20More%20technically%2C%20pink%20noise%0A%20%20is%20parameterized%20on%20a%20variable%20%3Ci%3E%CE%B1%3C%2Fi%3E%20(alpha)%3B%20at%20a%20given%0A%20%20frequency%20%3Ci%3Ef%3C%2Fi%3E%2C%20the%20amplitude%20is%201%2F%3Ci%3Ef%3Csup%3E%20%CE%B1%3C%2Fsup%3E%3C%2Fi%3E.%0A%20%20%3Ci%3E%CE%B1%3C%2Fi%3E%20can%20range%20from%200%20to%202%20(inclusive).%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%0A%3Cp%3E%0A%20%20For%20%22normal%22%20pink%20noise%20%E2%80%94%20what%20is%20sometimes%20imprecisely%20just%0A%20%20called%20%22pink%20noise%22%20per%20se%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ci%3E%CE%B1%3C%2Fi%3E%20is%201%2C%20which%20means%0A%20%20that%20there%20is%20equal%20energy%20across%20all%20octaves.%20At%20the%20extreme%20of%0A%20%20%3Ci%3E%CE%B1%3C%2Fi%3E%20%3D%200%2C%20the%20generated%20noise%20is%20actually%20white%20noise%2C%20that%20is%2C%0A%20%20equal%20energy%20at%20all%20frequencies.%20At%20the%20other%20extreme%20of%0A%20%20%3Ci%3E%CE%B1%3C%2Fi%3E%20%3D%202%2C%20the%20generated%20noise%20is%20brown%20noise%2C%20which%20is%20an%0A%20%20integration%20over%20white%20noise%3B%20the%20waveform's%20instantaneous%20amplitude%0A%20%20takes%20the%20form%20of%20brownian%20motion.%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%0A%3Cp%3E%0A%20%20This%20tool%20allows%20you%20to%20adjust%20%3Ci%3E%CE%B1%3C%2Fi%3E%20as%20well%20as%20the%20overall%0A%20%20amplitude%20of%20the%20sound.%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%0A%3Cp%3E%0A%20%20%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Fgithub.com%2Fdanfuzz%2Fmimu%2Ftree%2Fmain%2Fpink-noise-explorer%22%3E%0A%20%20See%20the%20source%3C%2Fa%3E.%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%0A%3Ch3%3EItems%20of%20note%3C%2Fh3%3E%0A%0A%3Cp%3E%0A%20%20At%20higher%20%3Ci%3E%CE%B1%3C%2Fi%3E%2C%20there%20is%20relatively%20high%20energy%20in%20the%0A%20%20very-low%20frequency%20range.%20This%20can%20cause%20the%20waveform%20to%20wander%0A%20%20significantly%20out%20of%20the%20valid-for-audio%20range%20-1%20to%201.%20This%20demo%0A%20%20adjusts%20for%20that%20implicitly%3A%20As%20you%20raise%20%3Ci%3E%CE%B1%3C%2Fi%3E%2C%20the%20overall%0A%20%20amplitude%20is%20adjusted%20downward.%20It's%20not%20a%20perfect%20adjustment%2C%20though%2C%0A%20%20so%20you%20might%20find%20that%20you%20need%20to%20manually%20adjust%20amplitude%20up%20or%0A%20%20down%2C%20depending%20on%20what%20you're%20aiming%20for.%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%0A%3Cp%3E%0A%20%20True%20brown%20noise%20(%3Ci%3E%CE%B1%3C%2Fi%3E%20%3D%202)%20is%20not%20actually%20fruitful%20when%0A%20%20turned%20into%20an%20audio%20waveform%2C%20but%20it%20can%20still%20be%20fun%20to%20look%20at.%0A%20%20However%2C%20don't%20be%20surprised%20if%20you%20end%20up%20looking%20at%20an%20empty%0A%20%20display%20when%20the%20waveform%20strays%20far%20out%20of%20range%20(per%20the%20previous%0A%20%20note).%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%0A%3Cp%3E%0A%20%20The%20noise%20is%20generated%20in%20this%20demo%20by%20using%20an%20IIR%20(infinite%20impulse%0A%20%20response)%20filter%20with%20five%20poles.%20The%20result%20is%20not%20mathematically%0A%20%20100%25%20accurate%2C%20however%20this%20is%20generally%20considered%20close%20enough%20for%0A%20%20most%20audio%20applications.%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%0A%3Ctable%20class%3D%22footer%22%3E%0A%20%20%3Ctbody%3E%3Ctr%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%3Ctd%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20Copyright%202015-2025%20the%20Mimu%20Authors%20(Dan%20Bornstein%20et%20alia).%3Cbr%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20SPDX-License-Identifier%3A%20Apache-2.0%0A%20%20%20%20%3C%2Ftd%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%3Ctd%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Fmilk.com%2F%22%3Emilk.com%3C%2Fa%3E%20%2F%20%3Ca%20href%3D%22..%2F%22%3Emimu%3C%2Fa%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%3C%2Ftd%3E%0A%20%20%3C%2Ftr%3E%0A%3C%2Ftbody%3E%3C%2Ftable%3E%0A%0A%0A%0A%3C%2Fbody%3E%0A%3C%2Fbo